  "about": {
    "title": "About AnimeEnigma",
    "subtitle": "A self-hosted anime streaming platform",
    "faqs": {
      "q1": {
        "q": "What is AnimeEnigma?",
        "a": "AnimeEnigma is a self-hosted anime streaming platform with Shikimori and MAL integration. It combines metadata from Shikimori with video from multiple sources, plus tools like recommendations, OP/ED ratings, watch parties, and personal lists — all in one place."
      },
      "q2": {
        "q": "Is it free? Are there ads?",
        "a": "Yes, free and ad-free. The platform is self-hosted by a small group, not a commercial service. There's no advertising, no tracking pixels, and no subscription tier — everyone gets the same access."
      },
      "q3": {
        "q": "Where do the videos come from?",
        "a": "AnimeEnigma streams videos from Kodik and AnimeLib (Russian audio/subs). The backend proxies the streams so your IP never hits the external CDN directly. English-source players are being rebuilt — new providers are coming."
      },
      "q4": {
        "q": "How do recommendations work?",
        "a": "We combine five signals: top-list similarity (S1), genre affinity (S2), global trending (S3), rating boost (S4), and seasonal freshness (S5). Each signal contributes a weighted score and the final list is mixed. No personal data leaves the server — recommendations are computed locally from your activity."
      },
      "q5": {
        "q": "Can I import my MAL list?",
        "a": "Yes. Go to Profile → Settings → MAL Import and enter your MAL username. The importer pulls your full list (statuses, scores, episodes watched, dates) and resolves each title to the AnimeEnigma catalog. Re-running the import updates entries that changed on MAL."
      },
      "q6": {
        "q": "Is there a mobile app?",
        "a": "Not yet — the web app is fully mobile-responsive and works offline-ish via the browser cache. A native app may come later, but for now installing the site as a PWA (Add to Home Screen) is the closest thing."
      },
      "q7": {
        "q": "How do I report a bug or request a feature?",
        "a": "Use the \"Send feedback\" link in the page footer — pick Bug, Issue, or Feature, optionally describe it, and submit. The report is saved on the server and an admin gets a Telegram notification. Console logs and network requests are auto-attached to help debugging."
      },
      "q8": {
        "q": "Who runs this site?",
        "a": "A small self-hosted group of anime fans. The code is open and contributions are welcome via the project repository. No company, no shareholders, no roadmap pressure — just folks who wanted a better way to watch anime."
      }
    }
  },
